President Barack Obama will award Kyle J. White, a former Army Sergeant, the Medal of Honor for his courageous actions in Afghanistan in 2007. White, who served as a Platoon Radio Telephone Operator, will be the seventh living recipient of the Medal of Honor for actions in Iraq or Afghanistan. He will be honored for his selfless service and bravery. White currently works as an Investment Analyst in Charlotte, NC. The Medal of Honor is awarded to members of the Armed Forces who demonstrate gallantry and self-sacrifice beyond the call of duty.